                     <interp inst="def1-473-18540403" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY MARDELL</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18540403-473-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18540403-473-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18540403-473-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>, stealing 6 lbs. weight of suet; the goods of <persName id="t18540403-name-120" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-120" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-120" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-120" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18540403-473-offence-1 t18540403-name-120"></join>William Roberts</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540403-name-121" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-121" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-121" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-121" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a butcher. On Wednesday evening, 8th March, I lost some suet—this (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is it—it weighs about 7 lbs.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540403-name-122" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-122" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-122" type="surname" value="HARRINGTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-122" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HARRINGTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, N</hi> 29). On Wednesday evening, 8th March, I saw the prisoner—a boy named Giles was with him—he had one lump of suet—the prisoner had a bundle containing three kidneys of suet—I asked him where he got it—he said he had got it from a countryman, and had given 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540403-name-123" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-123" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-123" type="surname" value="GILES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-123" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GILES</persName>
                  </hi>. I know the prisoner. On Wednesday evening, 8th March, between 7 and 8 o'clock, I saw him go into Mr. Roberta's shop and take some suet—he brought it out in his arms, and put it in a handkerchief—I did not get any of it—I was carrying a piece for him when the policeman saw me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did not you give me the suet? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, I did not steal it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> What he says is false; the prosecutor said himself that he would not believe that I took it out of the shop, the door has a bell to it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540403-name-124" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-124" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-name-124" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I said I did not think he could possibly get in without the bell ringing—there is a bell to the door.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185404030027"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">The prisoner's statement before the Magistrate was read, as follows:</hi> "The boy Giles took the suet as well as me; he was not carrying the suet for me, but for himself."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I never took it; a boy saw Giles take it, but said he would not have anything to do with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18540403-473-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-473-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540403-473-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">The prisoner was further charged with having been before convicted.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">WILLIAM BACON></hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi>, 482). I produce a certificate—(<hi rend="italic">read: "Henry Mardell, convicted here June</hi>, 1853, <hi rend="italic">of larceny.—
Confined Six Months"</hi>)—the prisoner is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi>. Aged 17.—<hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18540403-473-punishment-18" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18540403-473-punishment-18" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
